			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There is alot of hype about the 15 wieght issue.<BR>
I am a level 13 monk, and I just now got a full suit of<BR>
Mesh.  The AC you get with full leather, is higher, <BR>
than Keeping your wieght below 15, but there is still<BR>
plenty of reason to keep your wieght down.  Upon getting<BR>
below 15 AC I immediately noticed the difference.  First off<BR>
My dual Wield fired more often, Doing more damage. My Dodge and<BR>
Block skills also fire more often, (which are not <BR>
figured into your AC).  Making me harder to hit.  Also I pumped all <BR>
my points into strength, and I am satisfied, with it, especially since<BR>
I can usually find plenty of people willing to cast <BR>
Buffs on me, (Sometimes doubling my hit points and AC.) So beg your<BR>
fellow players to cast spells on you.  I have been able to solo <BR>
Yellows, With the right Buffs....  <BR>
<BR>

				</font>
